Title: Black Holes in the Gauge Theoretic Formulation of Dilatonic Gravity
Authors: Marcelo M. Leite and Victor O. Rivelles
Comments: Action is improved to be reparametrization invariant. Misprintings
  corrected. 10 pages, Latex
Report-no: IFUSP-P/1229
Journal-ref: Phys.Lett. B392 (1997) 305-310
\\
  We show that two-dimensional topological BF theories coupled to particles
carrying non-Abelian charge admit a new coupling involving the Lagrange
multiplier field. When applied to the gauge theoretic formulation of dilatonic
gravity it gives rise to a source term for the gravitational field. We show
that the system admits black hole solutions.
